Date:  0/0/1953
Source:  Story of the Kauri, The
Author:  REED
Vol / Page:  61
Edition:
Quote:  The sapling [of kauri] is known as a `ricker', sometimes incorrectly spelt `rika' It is not, however, of Maori origin, but an old Anglo-Saxon term applied to a pole used  in making hay-ricks, or to the spar of a boat. The name was probably first applied to the young kauri by the men of the Royal Navy in search of ships' spars.
