Quote:  Rikka, the bushman's word for a young kauri, long supposed to be a Maori word, turns out to be an English dialect word for a pole, apparently introduced by workers from England in the kauri timber trade as long  ago as the 1790s.
Notes:  (Wall NZ Speech)

